description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_msg.c
Lines: 469-476 and 780-787

The CBOR decoding uses an unusual backtracking pattern:
```c
} else {
    /* Skip unknown key-value pair */
    (void)zcbor_pop_error(zsd);
    *zsd = key_state;
    if (!zcbor_any_skip(zsd, NULL) ||
        !zcbor_any_skip(zsd, NULL)) {
        goto bad_request;
    }
}
```

Problems:
1. zcbor_pop_error() is called unconditionally even if there's no error state
2. State is restored to key_state but key has already been decoded, so zcbor_any_skip skips the key again (double skip)
3. This leaves the decoder in incorrect position

The intent seems to be: skip the unknown key-value pair. But the implementation reads the key, then if unknown, restores state and skips key+value. This is fragile and may misparse complex CBOR.

Category: CORRECTNESS - parsing logic error
